dc_title_s: Insurance maps of Hudson County, New Jersey : vol. 8
dc_description_s: Includes title sheet, key, streets and specials index, index map, and text. Title in upper margin of sheets: West Hoboken. Index map on double sheet. "Volume 8 comprising Weehawken, West Hoboken, Town of Union, West New York, Guttenberg, North Bergen & Secaucus, Hudson Co., N.J." "West Hoboken was a municipality that existed in Hudson County, New Jersey, United States, from 1861 to 1925 ... On January 1, 1925, Union City was formed, replacing both Union Hill and West Hoboken."-- Wikipedia.
dc_publisher_s: New York : Sanborn-Perris Map Co., Limited, 1900.
